<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="546" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1826,2031]" box="[151,751,1826,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1826,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 
<quantity box="[664,747,1827,1851]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1826,2031]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">
Crown dull ochraceous, face mainly reddish brown with black tinge, transverse brown band across eye, anteclypeus yellowish, lora and genae white, ocelli reddish brown (
<figureCitation box="[927,1002,1898,1923]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,436,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,426,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia fusca sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia lactata sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241681/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">
Figs. 
<number box="[992,1002,1899,1923]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
G, H). Pronotum brown. Mesoscutum dark brown, basal triangles black, lateral margins and scutellum yellowish. Forewing hyaline with brownish tinge, broad band along costa except a subapical oval area, black (
<figureCitation box="[849,916,1970,1995]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,436,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,426,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia fusca sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia lactata sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241681/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">
Fig. 
<number box="[905,916,1971,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Mesepimeron dark brown. Legs and hind tibial macrosetae yellowish.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" targetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1673,1787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1673,1695]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[286,456,1674,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[286,456,1674,1695]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">Busonia curvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[465,548,1673,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[465,548,1673,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1136,1703,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[991,1136,1703,1726]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">Busonia fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1143,1225,1704,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1143,1225,1704,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1826,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
Male genitalia. Pygofer with dorsoanterior margin rounded, posterior angle broadly rounded. Appendage of segment X slender spinelike, at 
<number box="[516,526,1865,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[535,551,1865,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="4.0">4</number>
th curved posteriorly and reaching posterior margin, in posterior view crossing midline. Subgenital plate with row of setae on dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[862,930,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1434,175,1667]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia fusca sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
Fig. 
<number box="[916,930,1902,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Style with a few setae on dorsal margin, apex pointed. Connective manubrium slender, central lobe triangular. Aedeagus apex rounded, with atrial region as long as shaft, dorsal region curved, with small triangle on dorsal margin; aedeagal shaft broad and rounded in basal half, gonopore narrow in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[591,667,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1434,175,1667]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia fusca sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
Figs. 
<number box="[654,667,2010,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
F, G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1015,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,501]" box="[199,1015,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">Etymology.</emphasis>
