<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker" authorityName="Baker" box="[611,837,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis box="[611,759,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">B. scutellaris</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[768,837,439,464]" name="United States Pacific Island Wildlife Refuges" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">Baker</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having the anteclypeus yellowish, lora and gena white, and aedeagus apex and base rounded.
</paragraph>
